---> Switching Attacks : 

1) Man-in-the-Middle/On-Path Attacks
2) MAC Cloning
3) MAC Flooding Attacks

The solution: 
   MAC Filtering and MAC Limiting
   The IEEE 802.1X standard defines a port-based network access control (PNAC) mechanism.

   

---> Routing Attacks :
   1) router spoofing : Man-in-the-Middle Attack,Traffic Redirecting Attack




---> Wireless Infrastructure:

1) ROGUE ACCESS POINTS AND EVIL TWINS
2) JAMMING ATTACKS



---> Server Attacks :
 1) DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service

 The solution:  Load Balancers
 
